  "texts": [
    "The worker also implements a lazy dropping policy at the queue where requests that are too late to be processed by the current DNN will be dropped directly without further processing (similar to (Shen et al. 2019; Gujarati et al. 2020)).",
    "We exclusively employ GPUs for the DNN inference task analogous to other serving systems (Shen et al. 2019; Gujarati et al. 2020).",
    "Our system and algorithms equally apply to CPUs or other accelerators, provided that the predictability and stability of inference latencies hold.",
    "Worker manager The worker manager is responsible for deploying and adapting DNNs on the workers.",
    "Supplied with the DNN selection decision made by the scheduler, the worker manager fetches the DNN from the DNN zoo and loads the DNN (moving from the host memory to the GPU memory) on the GPU of the worker."
  ],
